CAPE TOWN - Cape Town sports stars have contributed to their communities as the nation celebrates Nelson Mandela’s centenary. Habitat for Humanity in association with the Nelson Mandela Foundation aims to build 100 homes around the country, all in the name of Madiba. On Mandela’s birthday some of the country’s biggest sports stars give their 67 minutes to the community of Mfuleni in the Western Cape. READ: Mandela-mania takes London by storm Players from Premier Soccer League side Cape Town City, cricket franchise the Cape Cobras, Western Province Rugby and the Springboks all got their hands dirty as they built a house in the informal settlement just outside of Cape Town. eNCA sports reporter Moeti Moeti has more. Click on the video gallery above to watch. eNCA